{
  "local_port": 42260,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I act while in college?",
  "response": "College is a transformative time in your life, offering opportunities for personal, academic, and social growth. Here are some tips on how to act and make the most of your college experience:\n\n### **1. Prioritize Your Academics**\n   - **Attend Classes Regularly:** Even if attendance isn\u2019t mandatory, showing up helps you stay engaged and learn better.\n   - **Stay Organized:** Use planners or apps to manage assignments, exams, and deadlines.\n   - **Seek Help When Needed:** Don\u2019t hesitate to ask professors, TAs, or classmates for help. Utilize campus resources like tutoring centers or study groups.\n   - **Stay Curious:** Take courses that genuinely interest you, and explore subjects outside your major.\n\n### **2. Build Relationships**\n   - **Be Friendly and Approachable:** Smile, introduce yourself, and engage in conversations with classmates and professors.\n   - **Network:** Attend events, join clubs, and connect with people who share your interests or career goals.\n   - **Respect Diversity:** College is a melting pot of cultures, beliefs, and backgrounds. Be open-minded and respectful of differences.\n\n### **3. Manage Your Time Wisely**\n   - **Balance Work and Play:** Allocate time for studying, socializing, hobbies, and self-care.\n   - **Avoid Procrastination:** Break tasks into smaller chunks and tackle them early to reduce stress.\n   - **Set Goals:** Short-term and long-term goals help you stay focused and motivated.\n\n### **4. Take Care of Yourself**\n   - **Get Enough Sleep:** Avoid pulling all-nighters regularly; a well-rested mind performs better.\n   - **Eat Well:** Choose nutritious meals and avoid excessive junk food or caffeine.\n   - **Exercise Regularly:** Physical activity boosts your mood and energy levels.\n   - **Prioritize Mental Health:** If you\u2019re feeling overwhelmed, seek support from campus counseling services or trusted friends.\n\n### **5. Get Involved**\n   - **Join Clubs or Organizations:** This is a great way to meet people, develop skills, and explore interests.\n   - **Volunteer or Intern:** Gain experience and give back to the community.\n   - **Attend Events:** Explore campus activities, lectures, and performances to broaden your horizons.\n\n### **6. Be Responsible**\n   - **Manage Finances:** Budget wisely, avoid unnecessary debt, and take advantage of student discounts.\n   - **Stay Safe:** Be aware of your surroundings, especially at night, and follow campus safety guidelines.\n   - **Be Honest:** Avoid plagiarism, cheating, or unethical behavior in your academic and personal life.\n\n### **7. Embrace Independence**\n   - **Take Ownership:** College is a time to learn self-reliance. Take responsibility for your decisions and actions.\n   - **Step Out of Your Comfort Zone:** Try new things, whether it\u2019s a class, hobby, or social activity.\n   - **Learn from Mistakes:** It\u2019s okay to fail or make errors\u2014use them as opportunities to grow.\n\n### **8. Plan for the Future**\n   - **Explore Career Options:** Visit the career center, attend job fairs, and seek internships or part-time jobs related to your field of interest.\n   - **Build a Resume:** Start early by gaining skills, experiences, and connections that will help you after graduation.\n   - **Stay Adaptable:** Be open to changing your major or career path if you discover new passions.\n\n### **9. Be Authentic**\n   - **Be Yourself:** Don\u2019t feel pressured to conform to others\u2019 expectations. Embrace your unique personality and values.\n   - **Stand Up for What\u2019s Right:** Advocate for yourself and others, and take a stand against injustice or unfair treatment.\n\n### **10. Enjoy the Journey**\n   - **Create Memories:** College is a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Make friends, try new things, and have fun (responsibly).\n   - **Stay Present:** Don\u2019t stress too much about the future\u2014focus on making the most of your time now.\n\nRemember, college is about growth and exploration. Be open to learning, take initiative, and enjoy the journey!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
